Texas International Inc said ithas received an unqualified audit opinion from auditor ArthurAndersen and Co.    The company had received a qualified opinion on 1985financial statements subject to its ability to resolvenegotiations with its U.S. bank group.  Subsequently, it soldalmost all its domestic oil and natural gas properties andretired all U.S. bank debt in March 1987 with part of theproceeds. Reuter&#3;